iology.stackexchange.com/users/4697/kuzzooroo","reputation":235,"display_name":"kuzzooroo","accept_rate":60},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fcf9d3bdac2c3fa35177730c31b34f79?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6307/canadianer","reputation":6147,"display_name":"canadianer"},"score":1,"post_id":28615,"edited":false,"creation_date":1424119263,"comment_id":47175,"body":"Plants store sugar as starch and use it to make cellulose (for their cell wall). It&#39;s also important to realize that sugar is only one of the products of photosynthesis. The Calvin cycle produces 3 carbon molecules which can feed into other metabolic pathways such as for amino acid or nucleoside synthesis. Basically it&#39;s the source of all carbon in plants."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fcf9d3bdac2c3fa35177730c31b34f79?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6307/canadianer","reputation":6147,"display_name":"canadianer"},"score":0,"post_id":28615,"edited":false,"creation_date":1424119858,"comment_id":47176,"body":"I just realized my other comment may have been misleading. Of course they use all of the sugar they produce, just not as energy."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ce583a4e598d96791baf95e5e4082534?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4697,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4697/kuzzooroo","reputation":235,"display_name":"kuzzooroo","accept_rate":60},"score":1,"post_id":28615,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fcf9d3bdac2c3fa35177730c31b34f79?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6307/canadianer","reputation":6147,"display_name":"canadianer"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1424128404,"comment_id":47182,"body":"@