plit the trypsin stock into small aliquots, so you don't have to thaw out the whole bottle everytime you split your cells.<\/p>\n","answer_id":28463,"question_id":28462,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/28462/what-is-trypsin","last_activity_date":1423524071,"creation_date":1423523845,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is Trypsin?","body":"<p>I am currently helping a PhD student in his research lab. We have been using Trypsin for the past couple of weeks but I am unsure of its purpose.\nI was wondering how Trypsin functioned and what it was usually used for?\nThe Trypsin we had been using apparently had \"gone bad\" and therefore we have to start the experiment over again. What could have caused it to not function properly? <\/p>\n","question_id":28462,"tags":["cell-biology","lab-reagents"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":1,"closed_reason":"off-topic","is_answered":true,"view_count":179,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/889548c1e8387b3d381853dee5212cfd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3632,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3632/shigeta","reputation":22684,"display_name":"shigeta","accept_rate":86},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/222b478bab6d59dc5de514a87dba88cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":389,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/389/bobthejoe","reputation":4911,"display_name":"bobthejoe","accept_rate":53},"score":1,"post_id":2651,"edited":false,"creation_date":1340182696,"comment_id":3792,"body":"Here is the original article. I&#39;m going to get working on that OWW article. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2235490\" rel=\"nofollow\">ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2235490<\/a>"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ca1772e52fe312c1d71f29b80e1937a3?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":1032,"link":"http://biology.stack