wn as <em>Spinochordodes tellinii<\/em> . Good music for a parasitic event like that by the way. Nematomorpha is the phylum. <\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/f7hMq.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n\n<p>If your a molecular guy, check out <em>Spinochordodes tellinii<\/em> and the WNT pathway, pretty cool stuff.<\/p>\n","answer_id":28425,"question_id":28422,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1423388039}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/28422/can-anyone-identify-the-worm-in-this-video-clip","last_activity_date":1423388039,"creation_date":1423363698,"answer_count":1,"title":"Can anyone identify the worm in this video clip?","body":"<p>My wife came across this youtube clip of a spider and a <a href=\"http://youtu.be/4E5vUUtSWT4\" rel=\"nofollow\">worm<\/a>. Can anyone identify at least the phylum? <\/p>\n","question_id":28422,"tags":["zoology","species-identification"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":28425,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":68,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/gL1Ev.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4461,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4461/saikanth-k","reputation":31,"display_name":"SaiKanth K"},"closed_date":1379105778,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/934a90404fe944a01135142de991d393?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4199,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4199/von-mises","reputation":746,"display_name":"von Mises"},"score":1,"post_id":10414,"edited":false,"creation_date":1379089382,"comment_id":13774,"body":"Im not sure this is true. How does one measure &#39;attraction&#39; anyways? And maybe the relationship has nothing to do with it. Maybe a guys who are desirable tend to be in more relationships, simply because they are desirable"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/gL1Ev.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":44