 cells?<\/p>\n\n<p>I was trying to collect cells to prepare them for cell binding studies to antibodies and then assess the cells on a filterplate. Typically, you keep them on ice to pause the metabolic state as well as to prevent endocytosis of the bound molecules. However, that shift seems to cause settling. How do you troubleshoot the appropriate temperature to process cells and what are the usual scientific justification for making such decisions.<\/p>\n","question_id":1688,"tags":["cell-culture"],"score":7,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":231,"up_vote_count":7,"last_edit_date":1423263238},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/6JGZf.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":8500,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8500/ladislav-nado","reputation":109,"display_name":"Ladislav Nado","accept_rate":100},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":28256,"edited":false,"creation_date":1422876619,"comment_id":46236,"body":"You can check <a href=\"http://beheco.oxfordjournals.org/content/13/1/20.full\" rel=\"nofollow\">this<\/a> paper out. I used the keyword &quot;pack size threshold&quot;"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/6JGZf.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":8500,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8500/ladislav-nado","reputation":109,"display_name":"Ladislav Nado","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":28256,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"edited":false,"creation_date":1422894309,"comment_id":46253,"body":"Hi @WYSIWYG! Close, but no cigar